WEBVTT

00:02.190 --> 00:04.090
LINDSAY:
Previously on "The Practice"...

00:04.090 --> 00:06.020
- Dad.

00:06.020 --> 00:07.180
- The principal says he got
a phone tip from a parent.

00:07.180 --> 00:09.130
Something about you dealing.
- I wasn't dealing.

00:09.130 --> 00:10.160
That's a lie.

00:10.160 --> 00:12.040
- Were they your drugs?
- No.

00:12.040 --> 00:13.140
- Then why were they
in your locker?

00:13.140 --> 00:15.100
- I don't know,
maybe I was set up.

00:15.100 --> 00:16.200
- Do you like my clock?

00:16.200 --> 00:19.110
It has a tiny camera in it,
a nanny cam.

00:19.110 --> 00:21.050
Two nights ago,
I come home,

00:21.050 --> 00:22.110
and I find this.

00:22.110 --> 00:23.150
- I'll meet him at 4:30.

00:23.150 --> 00:24.150
He's gonna give me eight bags.

00:24.150 --> 00:26.020
- But what if I get busted?

00:26.020 --> 00:27.210
KENDALL: My dad says,
"If you get caught,

00:27.210 --> 00:29.190
"never admit to anything,
even to your lawyer,

00:29.190 --> 00:31.220
because they'll be stuck
with whatever you tell 'em."

00:31.220 --> 00:33.220
- Who gave you the drugs?

00:33.220 --> 00:35.000
- Goes by Robby G.

00:35.000 --> 00:36.010
I don't know his full name.

00:36.010 --> 00:37.140
- Robby G.
- You know him?

00:37.140 --> 00:38.230
- He might work
for a client of mine.

00:38.230 --> 00:40.150
I'm not sure.
- That's nice.

00:40.150 --> 00:43.220
Father and son
both work for the same guy.

00:43.220 --> 00:45.170
I told my lawyer
I could handle this,

00:45.170 --> 00:48.060
but I forgot to ask whether
I needed witnesses to do this.

00:48.060 --> 00:49.150
- To do what?

00:49.150 --> 00:52.150
- To serve you
with this petition.

00:52.150 --> 00:54.090
- Change child custody?

00:54.090 --> 00:55.180
- I don't think you've been
a positive influence

00:55.180 --> 00:56.160
in Kendall's life.

01:01.130 --> 01:03.060
- I expect we'll do okay.

01:03.060 --> 01:05.209
No judge likes
to cut off custody,

01:05.209 --> 01:09.190
but Eugene, we could be
in for a real fight here.

01:09.190 --> 01:12.120
- I know.
- She hired Solomon Tager.

01:12.120 --> 01:13.140
Where she got the money
to do that,

01:13.140 --> 01:14.140
I don't know.

01:14.140 --> 01:15.170
What I do know is,

01:15.170 --> 01:19.030
this guy doesn't fool around.

01:19.030 --> 01:22.230
If I have to get ugly,
you have to let me.

01:22.230 --> 01:24.190
- I don't want you
tearing her up, Bobby.

01:24.190 --> 01:27.030
At the end of the day,
she's still my son's mother.

01:27.030 --> 01:28.100
- And at the end
of the day,

01:28.100 --> 01:31.200
we want you
to still be his father.

01:31.200 --> 01:33.020
- Dad?

01:33.020 --> 01:34.130
- Kendall,
what are you doing here?

01:34.130 --> 01:35.130
- I just came.

01:35.130 --> 01:36.130
I took the T.

01:36.130 --> 01:37.210
- Your mother know?

01:37.210 --> 01:39.100
- No.

01:43.020 --> 01:44.110
What's going on?

01:44.110 --> 01:46.040
I had to meet with
those doctors and stuff.

01:46.040 --> 01:47.230
Why is nobody telling me
what's going on?

01:53.210 --> 01:57.010
- Your mother thinks,

01:57.010 --> 02:00.010
um, your getting involved
with drugs

02:00.010 --> 02:02.140
has something to do
with my influence,

02:02.140 --> 02:08.100
and she thinks it would be best

02:08.100 --> 02:11.060
if you didn't
spend time with me.

02:11.060 --> 02:12.170
- Ever?

02:12.170 --> 02:14.170
- Just for a while.

02:14.170 --> 02:17.030
- But you're my dad.

02:17.030 --> 02:18.070
- It isn't about that.

02:18.070 --> 02:19.050
It's--

02:23.060 --> 02:27.090
She's doing
what she thinks is best.

02:27.090 --> 02:30.110
She loves you just like I do.

02:30.110 --> 02:34.110
We just disagree on what's best.

02:34.110 --> 02:37.200
- And she asking some judge
to stop you from being with me?

02:41.110 --> 02:44.050
- Something like that, yeah.

02:52.040 --> 02:55.040
<i>[upbeat funky music]</i>

02:55.040 --> 03:03.020
<i>♪</i> ♪

03:39.190 --> 03:41.010
- Come on,
we're gonna be late.

03:41.010 --> 03:42.020
ELLENOR: We got
plenty of time, Eugene.

03:42.020 --> 03:43.080
BOBBY: Who's up first?

03:43.080 --> 03:45.040
- The guardian ad litem,
Tanya Morrison.

03:45.040 --> 03:46.200
She takes a strong position;
she's tough.

03:46.200 --> 03:48.100
LINDSAY: Who's the judge?
- Bender.

03:48.100 --> 03:50.090
EUGENE: Come on.

03:52.120 --> 03:55.030
- Ms. Gamble.
- Hi.

03:55.030 --> 03:56.180
- Hi.
- Uh, listen.

03:56.180 --> 03:58.140
Unfortunately we weren't able
to reach a plea,

03:58.140 --> 04:00.140
so we go to trial.

04:00.140 --> 04:01.180
- Okay.

04:01.180 --> 04:03.060
- I'll be putting you on first,

04:03.060 --> 04:05.000
and remember,
we talked about his attorney.

04:05.000 --> 04:06.210
Listen, I'll do what I can
to protect you,

04:06.210 --> 04:09.130
but the main thing:
you have to keep your composure.

04:09.130 --> 04:11.110
- Okay.

04:11.110 --> 04:13.040
- He won't let her
get brutalized up there.

04:13.040 --> 04:14.110
- This attorney's tough.

04:14.110 --> 04:16.000
He's known for trying anything.

04:16.000 --> 04:18.000
- She's gonna be attacked,
isn't she?

04:18.000 --> 04:20.000
- Well,
defendants get the right

04:20.000 --> 04:22.000
to confront their accusers,
Mr. Hayes,

04:22.000 --> 04:25.170
and this one will.

04:25.170 --> 04:28.070
- Kendall has
an above average IQ,

04:28.070 --> 04:31.010
but he appears to be lacking
some moral sensibility

04:31.010 --> 04:32.180
with regard to his behavior.

04:32.180 --> 04:34.080
- What do you mean, doctor?

04:34.080 --> 04:35.080
- With the drug arrest.

04:35.080 --> 04:37.080
He focuses on the illegal search

04:37.080 --> 04:39.170
rather than his own bad acts,

04:39.170 --> 04:41.200
and in lying to his parents
about it afterwards,

04:41.200 --> 04:45.050
he focuses on how his denial
skirted the truth.

04:45.050 --> 04:47.010
- Come on, doctor.

04:47.010 --> 04:50.120
Growing up, my children threw
every excuse imaginable at me.

04:50.120 --> 04:52.110
Isn't that just being a kid?

04:52.110 --> 04:54.230
- The normal kid understands
when he's done something wrong

04:54.230 --> 04:58.040
and uses the excuse
as a way to escape punishment.

04:58.040 --> 04:59.220
With Kendall,
it's almost as if

04:59.220 --> 05:03.120
he believes the excuse
nullifies the bad act,

05:03.120 --> 05:05.080
and therein lies the problem.

05:05.080 --> 05:08.090
- To what do you attribute
Kendall's behavior?

05:08.090 --> 05:10.080
- There could be
a lot of factors,

05:10.080 --> 05:12.030
but I do believe
a significant one

05:12.030 --> 05:14.220
derives from contact
with his father.

05:14.220 --> 05:16.050
- He's a bad role model?

05:16.050 --> 05:17.230
- I'm not saying that.

05:17.230 --> 05:19.210
Likely, he's a great role model.

05:19.210 --> 05:23.110
I'm saying that contact with him
is having a negative influence.

05:23.110 --> 05:26.040
- A good model
with a bad influence?

05:26.040 --> 05:28.150
- Mr. Young is
a criminal defense attorney.

05:28.150 --> 05:30.130
I certainly don't have
all the answers,

05:30.130 --> 05:33.010
but I know that Kendall
is somehow

05:33.010 --> 05:36.190
processing right and wrong
through his father's eyes,

05:36.190 --> 05:40.110
and it's resulting in a blurring
of the lines for him.

05:40.110 --> 05:42.220
- How many hours total
did you spend with Kendall?

05:42.220 --> 05:44.020
- About 6 1/2.

05:44.020 --> 05:46.120
- And in 6 1/2 hours,

05:46.120 --> 05:49.220
you find that Eugene Young
is a bad influence on his son?

05:49.220 --> 05:51.120
- Yes.

05:51.120 --> 05:53.020
- Because he's
a criminal defense attorney.

05:53.020 --> 05:55.040
- Because of the emotional
and behavioral impact

05:55.040 --> 05:56.200
he's had on his son.

05:56.200 --> 06:00.030
- Because he's
a criminal defense attorney.

06:00.030 --> 06:02.200
- Mr. Young
faces tough moral choices.

06:02.200 --> 06:05.070
Maybe he has a handle on it,
and maybe he doesn't.

06:05.070 --> 06:08.020
- When you say Mr. Young
faces tough moral choices,

06:08.020 --> 06:11.030
do you have any evidence
of Mr. Young acting amorally?

06:11.030 --> 06:12.070
- Well,
I think defending somebody

06:12.070 --> 06:13.230
accused of murder is perhaps--

06:13.230 --> 06:15.060
- It's immoral for
a criminal defense attorney

06:15.060 --> 06:16.230
to represent murder defendants?

06:16.230 --> 06:19.060
- I'm talking about how
it impacts on a child to see--

06:19.060 --> 06:21.000
- It's your opinion
that children can't process--

06:21.000 --> 06:22.110
- Your Honor, he's not
letting the witness finish.

06:22.110 --> 06:23.220
- I agree.

06:23.220 --> 06:26.220
Let her complete
her response, Mr. Donnell.

06:26.220 --> 06:30.090
- Of course every defendant
deserves representation.

06:30.090 --> 06:33.060
Most 11-year-olds
can appreciate this.

06:33.060 --> 06:35.160
I'm speaking as to
what's going on with Kendall.

06:35.160 --> 06:38.140
- Thank you, doctor, but how--
- I still haven't finished.

06:38.140 --> 06:40.120
By defending these people,

06:40.120 --> 06:43.070
the drug dealers,
the people that use drugs,

06:43.070 --> 06:46.110
Kendall sees an implied
endorsement of them.

06:46.110 --> 06:48.210
Dad says,
"These people are okay."

06:48.210 --> 06:52.040
Dad says, "What these people
did wasn't so bad."

06:52.040 --> 06:54.140
Dad says, "It's the police
who are at fault."

06:54.140 --> 06:57.140
These are the things
this kid is processing.

06:57.140 --> 07:00.150
It's not coming from his mother.

07:03.000 --> 07:05.150
- Thank you for taking the time.
- Sure.

07:05.150 --> 07:08.010
I'm going to have Lucy
take notes if you don't mind.

07:08.010 --> 07:09.020
- Sure.

07:09.020 --> 07:10.100
Well, as I said on the phone,

07:10.100 --> 07:12.110
I'm a practicing
child psychologist,

07:12.110 --> 07:14.190
and I was recently
discharged from my job

07:14.190 --> 07:17.140
for grounds I believe
to be illegal.

07:17.140 --> 07:19.010
- And what were the grounds?

07:19.010 --> 07:21.090
- I developed
a condition in my eyes,

07:21.090 --> 07:22.220
which they cited as cause.

07:22.220 --> 07:24.090
- What kind of condition?

07:24.090 --> 07:26.190
- It affects the muscles and--

07:26.190 --> 07:31.130
well, as you can see,
I'm rather cross-eyed.

07:36.130 --> 07:38.090
Can you tell?

07:38.090 --> 07:40.090
- Well, since you mention it.

07:40.090 --> 07:43.020
- And this is
why they fired you?

07:43.020 --> 07:44.040
- Yes.

07:44.040 --> 07:45.210
It's bilateral nerve palsy.

07:45.210 --> 07:47.170
I got it from a head trauma.

07:47.170 --> 07:51.050
Ms. Washington,
it does not render me disabled.

07:51.050 --> 07:54.090
I have been, and continue to be,
an excellent psychologist.

07:54.090 --> 07:56.000
I'm very good at what I do.

08:02.080 --> 08:05.020
- I spent most of the afternoon
walking around window shopping.

08:05.020 --> 08:06.020
Then I walked to my car.

08:06.020 --> 08:07.170
- And what happened?

08:07.170 --> 08:10.020
- As I started
to pull out, that man,

08:10.020 --> 08:12.120
he jumped in the passenger side.

08:12.120 --> 08:13.130
- What did you do?

08:13.130 --> 08:15.020
- I tried to jump out my side,

08:15.020 --> 08:17.080
but he grabbed my wrist
so I couldn't get out.

08:17.080 --> 08:18.170
- What happened then?

08:18.170 --> 08:20.040
- He pulled a knife
out of his jacket

08:20.040 --> 08:23.050
and pressed it
against my neck really hard.

08:23.050 --> 08:25.060
- Tell me, what was
going through your mind?

08:25.060 --> 08:27.160
- Fear.

08:27.160 --> 08:29.130
I was thinking,

08:29.130 --> 08:32.190
"If he had just wanted the car,
he would have let me jump out."

08:32.190 --> 08:34.230
I thought he was gonna hurt me.

08:34.230 --> 08:37.150
- What happened next?
- I started talking.

08:37.150 --> 08:39.140
- You started talking?
- Yes.

08:39.140 --> 08:41.010
I started telling him
about myself.

08:41.010 --> 08:43.100
I thought maybe
if he knew something about me,

08:43.100 --> 08:44.110
he wouldn't want to kill me.

08:44.110 --> 08:45.200
- Why did you think that?

08:45.200 --> 08:47.120
- I read that one strategy
with an attacker

08:47.120 --> 08:49.120
is to try to
humanize yourself with them

08:49.120 --> 08:51.110
so they won't kill you.

08:51.110 --> 08:53.150
- And it worked?

08:53.150 --> 08:55.140
- Yeah, I guess so,
because he told me to get out,

08:55.140 --> 08:58.180
which I did,
and then he drove away.

08:58.180 --> 09:00.220
- Any bruises on your wrist
or your neck?

09:00.220 --> 09:02.140
- I don't think so.

09:02.140 --> 09:04.160
- You never went to a hospital?
- No.

09:04.160 --> 09:06.230
- Can anybody account for your
whereabouts that afternoon,

09:06.230 --> 09:08.160
when you say you were
window shopping?

09:08.160 --> 09:10.130
- Not that I know of;
I was by myself.

09:10.130 --> 09:12.180
- Did you also
kiss Randy Strunk?

09:12.180 --> 09:14.140
- Excuse me?

09:14.140 --> 09:16.100
- The truth is, you met Randy,
you had consensual sex with him,

09:16.100 --> 09:17.220
and then
you loaned him your car.

09:17.220 --> 09:19.030
- Objection!
- Isn't that what happened?

09:19.030 --> 09:20.030
- Are you crazy?
- You would never

09:20.030 --> 09:21.110
sleep with someone you just met?

09:21.110 --> 09:22.160
- Objection!
- It's a fair question.

09:22.160 --> 09:23.150
- Sidebar, Your Honor.

09:31.130 --> 09:32.130
- She's been known
to pick up men,

09:32.130 --> 09:34.090
and not just with her car.

09:34.090 --> 09:36.070
- You've got to be kidding me.
- She's a social girl.

09:36.070 --> 09:38.150
I'm just showing--
- That is completely irrelevant.

09:38.150 --> 09:40.020
Even if it were true,

09:40.020 --> 09:41.100
a victim's sexual history
is inadmissible.

09:41.100 --> 09:43.000
Rape shield.
- This is not a rape.

09:43.000 --> 09:44.130
Rape shield doesn't apply,
and I am entitled

09:44.130 --> 09:46.100
to cross-examine
my client's accuser.

09:46.100 --> 09:48.000
- I won't let you go there,
Mr. Dawson.

09:48.000 --> 09:49.000
- You don't
know this woman, Judge.

09:49.000 --> 09:50.070
She's a real piece of--

09:50.070 --> 09:51.070
- Problem is, Counsel,
I know you.

09:51.070 --> 09:53.060
You're not going there.

09:58.010 --> 10:00.010
- He's a good man,
and in my opinion,

10:00.010 --> 10:01.150
a very good father.

10:01.150 --> 10:03.040
- Well, then why are we here?

10:03.040 --> 10:05.150
- We're here because of
the world he lives in.

10:05.150 --> 10:08.180
My ex-husband
fights for bad people.

10:08.180 --> 10:12.120
My son attributes
some idealism to this world.

10:12.120 --> 10:14.220
The influence scares me.

10:14.220 --> 10:17.020
He's begun to deal drugs

10:17.020 --> 10:18.140
with a sense of pride, even,

10:18.140 --> 10:21.020
a pride that he gets
from his dad.

10:21.020 --> 10:22.080
- Objecting that.

10:22.080 --> 10:23.210
- It would be one thing
if he came home

10:23.210 --> 10:25.130
wanting to defend criminals,

10:25.130 --> 10:28.030
but to identify with them
as role models?

10:28.030 --> 10:29.220
This is beginning to happen.

10:29.220 --> 10:32.030
- Have you talked
to your ex-husband about this?

10:32.030 --> 10:36.000
- My ex-husband
breathes this world.

10:36.000 --> 10:37.190
That's what led
to us splitting up.

10:37.190 --> 10:40.050
He's inside it.

10:40.050 --> 10:42.190
He defends these people
on a mission.

10:42.190 --> 10:45.120
It was more important to him
than being a husband,

10:45.120 --> 10:47.070
more important
than being a father.

10:47.070 --> 10:48.230
- Objection.
That isn't true, Sharon.

10:48.230 --> 10:50.230
JUDGE BENDER: Mr. Young.
- You know that's not true!

10:50.230 --> 10:52.210
- Mr. Young, take your seat.

10:54.070 --> 10:57.010
- I know you love him,

10:57.010 --> 10:59.220
but you don't see
what you're doing to him.

10:59.220 --> 11:03.010
JUDGE BENDER: Ms. Young, please
do not address your ex-husband.

11:07.090 --> 11:08.180
- That was a lie.
- It doesn't matter.

11:08.180 --> 11:10.000
- You just sat there.
- Eugene.

11:10.000 --> 11:11.210
- You just let her
go on with that.

11:11.210 --> 11:13.100
- I'll get my chance on cross.
- You should have shut her down!

11:13.100 --> 11:15.160
- Eugene, you know
she gets to tell her side.

11:15.160 --> 11:16.230
You know I had to let her.

11:16.230 --> 11:18.110
- She knows my values,

11:18.110 --> 11:20.000
she knows I don't honor
the people I defend,

11:20.000 --> 11:21.140
and she knows
Kendall knows that.

11:21.140 --> 11:24.030
- Tager probably told her
to come on strong.

11:24.030 --> 11:25.190
Like I said,
these kinds of fights

11:25.190 --> 11:28.050
you don't win by holding back.

11:28.050 --> 11:30.110
Eugene, look at me.

11:32.080 --> 11:34.130
Now it's my turn.

11:34.130 --> 11:37.080
I don't want to hold back.

11:37.080 --> 11:39.070
Anything you got on her
that I can use,

11:39.070 --> 11:42.050
now's the time to tell me.

11:42.050 --> 11:43.080
I'm friends with Sharon.

11:43.080 --> 11:44.130
I don't want to go after her,

11:44.130 --> 11:47.020
but if you want
your son back...

11:50.010 --> 11:51.180
I have no real choice.

11:55.130 --> 11:57.130
And you have to help me.

11:57.130 --> 12:00.130
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

12:00.130 --> 12:08.110
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:56.020 --> 12:57.180
- Bobby.
- Sharon.

12:57.180 --> 12:59.030
- It's okay.

12:59.030 --> 13:01.040
A second?

13:04.010 --> 13:06.050
Does he know why I'm doing this?

13:06.050 --> 13:11.020
- He understands
the reason you gave him, yes.

13:11.020 --> 13:13.100
Does he understand?

13:15.070 --> 13:17.030
- Do you?

13:17.030 --> 13:21.030
- I understand you think
you're doing what's best.

13:24.000 --> 13:25.010
I'll see you in there.

13:29.170 --> 13:31.030
- How long was it

13:31.030 --> 13:33.000
from the time Randy
allegedly got in the car

13:33.000 --> 13:34.180
to the time you got out?

13:34.180 --> 13:36.110
- It seemed like forever,
but it was probably

13:36.110 --> 13:37.200
no more than a couple minutes.

13:37.200 --> 13:40.110
- So you only had
a couple of minutes

13:40.110 --> 13:42.210
to reveal the personal details

13:42.210 --> 13:45.000
that you hoped
would spare your life?

13:45.000 --> 13:46.090
- Yes.

13:46.090 --> 13:47.210
- And the details
that you chose to reveal

13:47.210 --> 13:50.030
were, of course,
the ones that you thought

13:50.030 --> 13:52.130
would generate
the most sympathy?

13:52.130 --> 13:53.200
- I guess so, yes.

13:53.200 --> 13:55.140
- You told him
you had a settlement

13:55.140 --> 13:57.030
coming from a car accident,

13:57.030 --> 13:58.220
that you broke up
with your last boyfriend

13:58.220 --> 14:01.130
because you discovered he was
seeing one of your friends.

14:01.130 --> 14:02.230
And you have allergies.

14:02.230 --> 14:04.230
- I probably did.

14:04.230 --> 14:08.200
- Your favorite movie
is "Braveheart,"

14:08.200 --> 14:11.040
and you told him you lost
your virginity in a car.

14:11.040 --> 14:12.200
You tell him that?

14:12.200 --> 14:15.050
- I honestly don't remember
everything I said.

14:15.050 --> 14:16.080
I was scared.

14:16.080 --> 14:17.170
I was just rambling on.

14:17.170 --> 14:19.100
- Are those things true?

14:23.220 --> 14:25.220
If you're not sure,

14:25.220 --> 14:28.230
we can always verify them
with your insurance company,

14:28.230 --> 14:30.170
your friends, your doctor.

14:30.170 --> 14:32.040
- A lot of it is true.

14:32.040 --> 14:34.000
I was trying to talk to him
about my life,

14:34.000 --> 14:36.150
make him feel like he knew me.

14:39.040 --> 14:41.080
- What I did
was fax a demand letter

14:41.080 --> 14:44.090
plus a draft of a motion
for injunctive relief

14:44.090 --> 14:46.230
which we can bring
before a judge at any time.

14:46.230 --> 14:48.190
It did succeed
in getting their attention.

14:48.190 --> 14:50.050
- Which means?

14:50.050 --> 14:52.040
- Dr. Fairby,
your boss, and his lawyer

14:52.040 --> 14:53.210
are coming for a meeting.

14:53.210 --> 14:56.190
I suspect they could be offering
to modify your severance.

14:56.190 --> 14:58.170
- Well, that isn't what I--

15:04.150 --> 15:07.200
I really want my job back.

15:07.200 --> 15:10.190
- Okay, then,
I'll take the shot.

15:10.190 --> 15:12.080
- Thank you, Ms. Washington.

15:12.080 --> 15:15.010
- Okay, I'll call you
right after the meeting.

15:18.120 --> 15:20.160
I saw you snickering.
- I wasn't laughing.

15:20.160 --> 15:21.160
I--
- It's palsy, Jimmy.

15:21.160 --> 15:22.160
Real funny.

15:27.150 --> 15:29.170
- You're the one with
the primary physical custody

15:29.170 --> 15:30.170
right now,
aren't you, Sharon?

15:30.170 --> 15:32.050
- Yes.

15:32.050 --> 15:33.050
- You're the one spending

15:33.050 --> 15:34.180
the most time with Kendall.

15:34.180 --> 15:36.140
Possible you share
some blame for his problems,

15:36.140 --> 15:38.050
or is that just impossible?

15:38.050 --> 15:39.160
- I lived with Eugene
for nine years.

15:39.160 --> 15:41.150
I know where the blame goes.

15:41.150 --> 15:44.100
Plan B, I know that too.
- Plan B?

15:44.100 --> 15:45.230
What's that got to do
with Eugene's parenting?

15:45.230 --> 15:47.190
- It's got to do with Kendall
always bragging

15:47.190 --> 15:49.230
that his dad
can get anybody off.

15:49.230 --> 15:51.200
- He's a bad parent for the way
he defends his clients?

15:51.200 --> 15:53.070
- He's a bad influence

15:53.070 --> 15:55.140
when it comes to teaching him
accountability.

15:55.140 --> 15:57.000
- What about you,
as a primary caretaker,

15:57.000 --> 15:59.130
refusing to accept
any responsibility?

15:59.130 --> 16:01.210
What message on accountability
does that send?

16:01.210 --> 16:03.080
- I'm accepting responsibility

16:03.080 --> 16:05.140
to set my son's life
back on course.

16:05.140 --> 16:07.050
I'm taking the steps necessary

16:07.050 --> 16:10.030
to see that he's raised
with the right values.

16:10.030 --> 16:13.030
- So your concern in all this

16:13.030 --> 16:15.100
is that Kendall
learn the right values?

16:15.100 --> 16:16.100
- Yes.

16:16.100 --> 16:17.220
- And you don't think

16:17.220 --> 16:19.060
that Eugene is teaching
those values to Kendall?

16:19.060 --> 16:20.230
- No, I don't.

16:20.230 --> 16:22.030
- And values,
that's one of the reasons

16:22.030 --> 16:23.100
you got divorced.

16:23.100 --> 16:26.020
Your difference
of opinion on values?

16:30.200 --> 16:32.150
You had an affair,
didn't you, Sharon?

16:32.150 --> 16:33.220
- That was four years ago, and--

16:33.220 --> 16:35.030
- How long did that affair last?

16:35.030 --> 16:36.120
- Objection, Your Honor!

16:36.120 --> 16:37.210
What relevance is
an event that happened--

16:37.210 --> 16:39.100
- Excuse me,
but this witness is saying

16:39.100 --> 16:41.160
that my client's character
is deficient,

16:41.160 --> 16:43.200
and that his son
gleaned these deficiencies.

16:43.200 --> 16:47.110
I should be allowed to question
the petitioner on her character.

16:47.110 --> 16:49.170
- I'll allow it.

16:49.170 --> 16:52.060
Answer the question.

16:52.060 --> 16:54.100
- The affair
lasted about two months.

16:54.100 --> 16:56.150
- And during the affair,
on more than a few occasions,

16:56.150 --> 16:58.220
you told Eugene that you were
having dinner with a girlfriend,

16:58.220 --> 17:00.140
or you were working late,
when in fact,

17:00.140 --> 17:02.190
you were seeing this man;
isn't that right?

17:02.190 --> 17:04.190
- It was wrong.
I know that, but--

17:04.190 --> 17:07.099
- You were lying to him.
- Yes.

17:07.099 --> 17:09.180
- And did Kendall know
you were lying to his father?

17:09.180 --> 17:11.089
What kind of influence?

17:11.089 --> 17:13.010
- Kendall never found out about
either the affair or--

17:13.010 --> 17:14.060
- So your son
still doesn't know the truth.

17:14.060 --> 17:15.079
The deception lives on.

17:15.079 --> 17:16.180
- Objection.
- Withdrawn.

17:16.180 --> 17:18.079
The man you were seeing
was married, right?

17:18.079 --> 17:19.079
- Yes.

17:19.079 --> 17:20.089
- What kind of values does that

17:20.089 --> 17:21.119
teach your son, Sharon?

17:21.119 --> 17:23.050
What kind of values does he get

17:23.050 --> 17:24.200
from a mother's
infidelity and adultery?

17:24.200 --> 17:26.170
- Objection!
- Sustained.

17:26.170 --> 17:28.010
Move on.

17:28.010 --> 17:30.110
- You complained
about Eugene's job.

17:30.110 --> 17:32.100
You ever once ask him
to quit his job?

17:32.100 --> 17:34.020
- I knew he would never--

17:34.020 --> 17:35.100
- The question was,
did you ever ask him to quit?

17:35.100 --> 17:37.050
Yes or no?
- No, that doesn't--

17:37.050 --> 17:39.180
- You ever urge him
to demand to be made partner?

17:39.180 --> 17:41.190
That ever happen?
- Yes.

17:41.190 --> 17:45.070
- So this world he lives in,
which you so object to,

17:45.070 --> 17:48.170
you wanted him to become
a partner in it.

17:48.170 --> 17:50.140
You get alimony.
don't you, Sharon?

17:50.140 --> 17:51.140
- Yes.

17:51.140 --> 17:52.200
- You make money off this world,

17:52.200 --> 17:54.110
you urged him to go for partner,

17:54.110 --> 17:56.050
and now you cite that world

17:56.050 --> 17:58.060
as ground
for parental unfitness.

17:58.060 --> 18:00.170
Is hypocrisy a value
you pass on to Kendall?

18:00.170 --> 18:02.020
- Objection.
- Overruled.

18:02.020 --> 18:03.180
- The best interest
of the child, Sharon,

18:03.180 --> 18:06.070
does that include
infidelity, lying, hypocrisy?

18:06.070 --> 18:07.110
- Objection.
- Mr. Donnell.

18:07.110 --> 18:09.010
- After you drew
this conclusion

18:09.010 --> 18:10.090
that Eugene's job
wasn't good for Kendall,

18:10.090 --> 18:11.110
did you go to Eugene and say,

18:11.110 --> 18:12.200
"Hey, what do we
do about this?"

18:12.200 --> 18:14.230
Or did you just move
for full custody?

18:14.230 --> 18:16.060
- He's not going to change.

18:16.060 --> 18:17.210
- You just filed
for full custody

18:17.210 --> 18:19.030
without so much
as a conversation,

18:19.030 --> 18:20.220
didn't you, Sharon?

18:20.220 --> 18:22.110
Don't you think it could be
in Kendall's interest

18:22.110 --> 18:23.160
to try to work things out
with his dad

18:23.160 --> 18:24.160
before ripping him away?

18:24.160 --> 18:25.230
- He's badgering her!

18:25.230 --> 18:28.170
- Didn't Eugene
deserve that much?

18:28.170 --> 18:30.030
A conversation?
- Your Honor.

18:30.030 --> 18:31.140
- Didn't Kendall
deserve that much?

18:31.140 --> 18:35.000
- He's not going to change!

18:35.000 --> 18:38.000
